The Catholic Peace and Justice Commision has said it will distribute civic education materials during the season of Lent.The literature will be available to people of all denominations.The campaign aims to reinforce the church&rsquo;s agenda of ensuring Kenyans sail through this year&rsquo;s polls peacefully, Archbishop Martin Kivuva said on Wednesday.He spoke after celebrating Mass.The Kenya National Commission for Human Rights, the Muslim Human Rights Commission and Haki Yetu Commission have also partnered to raise awareness on the importance of civic education.During a forum held at the Holy Ghost Cathedral Hall in Mombasa, religious leaders called on Kenyans to demand accountability from their leaders and vote wisely.